On Santra, whose avarice was even greater than his gluttony.'

At once so greedy and so mean

As Santra nothing e'er was seen.

When he—the fruit. of ceaseless pains— At length an invitation gains

To a grand dinner, off he goes.

Once there, no modesty he knows. T-wice helped to titbits from the boar, He'll send his plate again for more.
